1 3. Be clearly marked and accompanied by appropriate signage to
2 warn drivers.
3 B. The Authority shall develop and adhere to safety standards
4 for the installation, operation, and maintenance of road spikes,
5 ensuring they do not pose a hazard to vehicles traveling in the
6 proper direction. The Authority shall conduct routine inspections
7 and maintenance to ensure the road spikes remain functional and
8 effective.
9 C. The Oklahoma Turnpike Authority is authorized to promulgate
10 any rules necessary to implement the provisions of this section.
11 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
